15/04/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- A pilot was killed when a warplane crashed during a training flight in western Turkey early on Wednesday (April 15th). 
The F-16 crashed near the Mustafakemalpasa district in the western province of Bursa after taking off from a base in the neighbouring province of Balikesir. 
Authorities are investigating the cause of the crash.
In other news, Somali pirates hijacked a Greek freighter in the Gulf of Aden on Tuesday, Greece's merchant marine ministry said. 
The ship is the Greek-operated MV Irene, flagged in Saint Vincent and the Grenadines. 
This is the ninth hijacking in the Gulf of Aden and the Indian Ocean this month. 
(CNNTurk, Hurriyet, Milliyet, Dogan news agency, AP, Xinhua - 15/04/09; ANA-MPA, AFP - 14/04/09)
